wer was allowed the Communists, when the Allies surrendered half of Europe to Russian control. Bad though things look to-day my husband is convinced that a Nazi control of the world would have been worse, and not only because of Hitler's mad-dog policy toward the Jews.

He asks you not to use his statements out of context which would produce a wrong impression.

Yours truly,

(Mrs. Vladimir Nabokov)





TO: STEWART H. SMITH1

